{% call components.section("Best practices") -%}

<h3>Including additional elements</h3>

<p>Don't use inconsistent amounts of content in stats that are grouped together.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-inconsistent-content.svg' | url }}" alt="Group containing a stat with icon only, stat without icon or title, and stat with title only"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 789px;" class="margin-top--2">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<p>However, a call to action does not have to appear under every stat in a group. Since it appears at the end of a stat, omitting it does not disrupt the positioning of other elements in a stat.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='light') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-ctas.svg' | url }}" alt="Group containing two stats with a call to action and one stat without"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 789px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<p>Don't use an icon that is unrelated to the body text.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-unrelated-icon.svg' | url }}" alt="Stat about telecom companies paired with a crab icon"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<h3>Character count</h3>
<p><strong>Title:</strong> Avoid character counts that cause the title to break into two lines at any screen size.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-long-title.svg' | url }}" alt="Stat with a title that wraps to two lines"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 381px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<p><strong>Number:</strong> Avoid character counts that cause the number to break into two lines at any screen size. If the number is a percentage, round up to avoid using decimals that would increase the character count.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-long-number.svg' | url }}" alt="Stat with a number that wraps to two lines"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 320px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<p><strong>Body text:</strong> Keep the body text as short and consumable as possible. Be mindful of lengthy character counts, especially when stats are grouped. In general, it is not recommended to have the stat's body text span more than 5 lines on small screens.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-long-body-text.svg' | url }}" alt="Stat with body text that is six lines long at mobile screen sizes"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 328px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<h3>Content guidelines</h3>

<p>If a title is used for one stat in a group, write a title for each stat. Ensure the title appears in the same slot for each grouped stat to keep formatting consistent.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-title-placement.svg' | url }}" alt="One row containing a stat with a title above the number, stat with no title, and stat with a title below number"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 789px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

<p>Avoid using 100% for more than one statistic in a group or on a page, unless you are able to cite a source and include footnotes.</p>

{% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
    <div class="centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-best-practice-100-percent-no-footnote.svg' | url }}" alt="Three stats with 100% and no footnote"
            style="--inline-img-max-width: 789px;">
    </div>
{%- endcall %}

{%- endcall %}

<hr class="margin-top--10 margin-bottom--10">

